    "scope_note": "The cataloged subject is Sir John Fortescue's twenty-chapter Middle English political treatise, composed or revised in the 1471-1476 period and represented by Charles Plummer's 1885 edition on printed pages 109-157. The record does not count the retained carrier title page, Plummer's introduction, critical apparatus, notes, or other omitted front and back matter as intrinsic work parts. The U-M XML's 412 PB milestones describe the full scanned carrier, while its verbal BODY encodes only the twenty chapters."
